#YAP #Pakistan hosted a thorough #training seminar on #AML Anti-Money Laundering, and #CFT Combating Financing of Terrorism at #HotelOne. Imparting awareness sessions benefits an organization to harness an in-depth AML/CFT culture to minimize the risk of any financial, reputational, regulatory or legal risk.

Staff training and awareness sessions are recognized as one of the most important controls to cater ML/TF risks as employees are the key performers and defensive to safeguard the institution from the menace of ML/TF. By getting sufficient knowledge from these sessions, the employees are capable of effectively recognizing red flags and suspicious activities.

The #Head of Compliance Department at YAP Pakistan shared a few words on his vision for such trainings: “Awareness session on ML/TF threats and associated vulnerabilities optimizes the scope of any organization to develop a shield with maximum potential and overthrow or bounce back any attempts by laundromats and Terrorist Financier in using the organization and its platform for any mala fide usage. Continuous awareness sessions and enhancement in learning create room for development for the organization and keep building higher and much potential brackets cater the threats from emerging challenges of ML/TF.

It is important that organizations should invest significantly in such trainings in order to be protected from any reputational and regulatory risk and relevant staff should be kept abreast, aware and train with the changing techniques and mechanism of ML/TF threats”.

Meharyab Niazi has 20 years of experience in the Financial Services and Information Technology industries across multiple geographical regions including United Kingdom, United Arab Emirates and Pakistan with a specific focus on financial inclusion, product development and strategic partnership management. He has a strong background in digital payments, prepaid cards and cross border remittances.

In 2018, Meharyab joined the founding team of YAP, a FinTech company based in UAE and in 2021 he assumed the role of CEO YAP Pakistan. He has been working on YAP’s international expansion plans for the Middle East, Africa and South-East Asia. Through YAP Pakistan, Meharyab aims to provide every Pakistani with a premium and seamless digital banking experience.
